{
  "stem": "15768.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He was also fluent in French so that we were able to leave the German end very much out of the picture.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And language, there was no issue.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I didn't have it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The principal in vain tried math, and in European math, divisions are done with the two little dots instead of the-- the little house that we use here in America with the larger number and the smaller number on either side.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And when they drew this little box for me with the divisor and things in it, I automatically-- I was good in math in Germany and in Belgium-- I automatically assumed it was square root.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And since I learned square root in Brussels, I proceeded to do a square root whereupon they were totally baffled in elementary school and pronounced that I didn't know math.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And so it was decreed I was going to go into the first grade.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And as I came into the first grade, the teacher made me sit on the dunce's chair, put the dunce's hat on.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I had no idea what this meant.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And took out her long pointer, and pointed to me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And said to her children, this is what a European looks like.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I didn't understand her, but I knew it wasn't very friendly.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "The kids all giggled.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "They were all first graders, and they thought it was extremely funny.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And there I was, lost, distressed, teary.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "To face the world by myself, really, in every way.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "After class-- there was one little black girl in the class, which was astounding because there were no black people in this town.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And it turned out that she was the daughter from a servant at a very well-to-do household.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
